==English==
===Etymology===
From mediaeval Latin [[elixir#Latin|elixir]], from Arabic {{ARchar|[[عكسير|العكسير]]}} (al-‘iksīr), from Greek [[ξήριον]] ‘medicinal powder’, from [[ξηρός]] ‘dry’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ɪˈlɪksə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|elixir|elixirs}}

#A sweet flavored liquid (usually containing a small amount of alcohol) used in compounding medicines to be taken by mouth in order to mask an unpleasant taste.
#A liquid which is believed to cure all ills and gives eternal life.
#A liquid which converts copper to gold.

